# Podman

> Podman is a plug'n'play docker replacement

- Sets the default machine podman will use (kinda)
`podman system connection default <machine-name>`

- Clones a docker image
`podman pull <image>`

- Attach interactively to a running container
`podman start -ia <container-name>`

- Sql Server
```
podman run 
    --name=mssqlserver 
    --hostname=mssql-server 
    --user=mssql -e 'ACCEPT_EULA=Y' 
    -e 'MSSQL_SA_PASSWORD=<your-password>' 
    -p 1433:1433 
    -v D:/Volumes/mssqlserver/data:/var/opt/mssql/data 
    -v D:/Volumes/mssqlserver/log:/var/opt/mssql/log 
    -v D:/Volumes/mssqlserver/secrets:/var/opt/mssql/secrets 
    -d mcr.microsoft.com/mssql/server:2022-latest
```
